# Rebuild on a Schedule

The documentation includes a section demonstrating how to implement scheduled rebuilds. According to the guide, you can use "a Worker with a [Cron Trigger](https://developers.cloudflare.com/workers/configuration/cron-triggers/) that rebuilds every hour."

## Example Implementation

The documentation provides code examples in both JavaScript and TypeScript for setting up this functionality:

**JavaScript version:**
```javascript
export default {
  async scheduled(event, env) {
    await fetch(env.DEPLOY_HOOK_URL, { method: "POST" });
  },
};
```

**TypeScript version:**
```typescript
export default {
  async scheduled(event: ScheduledEvent, env: Env): Promise<void> {
    await fetch(env.DEPLOY_HOOK_URL, { method: "POST" });
  },
};
```

Both implementations use the cron trigger feature to automatically send HTTP POST requests to your Deploy Hook URL at scheduled intervals, enabling automated builds without manual intervention.

